allNews.snippet: The market has been saturated and competitive for decades, but new shops keep coming with offerings like a taro doughnut from Hawaii.
allNews.lead_paragraph: The Donut Hole, in La Puente, doesn’t sell the very best doughnuts in the Los Angeles area, but I love going there. Driving through its absurd, gigantic fiberglass doughnut — a pristine example of mimetic architecture — is a brief, giddy and almost spiritual experience. It is half the joy of being there, and it gives the doughnuts a bit of an edge.

headline.main: Los Angeles Is a Doughnut Town

allNews.abstract: The former secretary of state on why the Republicans’ game with the debt ceiling is landing at a particularly perilous moment for the economy and for global security.
allNews.snippet: The former secretary of state on why the Republicans’ game with the debt ceiling is landing at a particularly perilous moment for the economy and for global security.
allNews.lead_paragraph: Speaker of the House Kevin McCarthy is making a ransom demand. His hostage is the economy and America’s credibility. Mr. McCarthy has threatened that House Republicans will refuse to raise the federal government’s debt ceiling, potentially triggering a global financial crisis, unless President Biden agrees to deep cuts to education, health care, food assistance for poor children and other services.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton: Republicans Are Playing Into the Hands of Putin and Xi

allNews.abstract: An ousted populist’s daughter seeks office, fueling concerns that the return of a divisive political dynasty may revive instability, too.
allNews.snippet: An ousted populist’s daughter seeks office, fueling concerns that the return of a divisive political dynasty may revive instability, too.
allNews.lead_paragraph: For close to two decades, the military and conservative establishment in Thailand has sought to keep former Prime Minister Thaksin Shinawatra and his supporters out of power. Mr. Thaksin, a populist politician and a business tycoon, was ousted in a coup in 2006 before he fled the country. Several years later, his sister succeeded him as prime minister and then suffered the same fate.

headline.main: Thailand’s Most Polarizing Family Rises Again Ahead of Election

headline.main: Ed Sheeran Trial: Did He Copy Marvin Gaye? Here’s What to Know.

allNews.snippet: Why do our female pop stars have to keep changing their clothes?
allNews.lead_paragraph: Oscar de la Renta. Versace. Alberta Ferretti. Roberto Cavalli. Elie Saab. Christian Louboutin. Zuhair Murad. Ashish. headline.main: Taylor Swift and the Sparkling Trap of Constant Reinvention
